edu.northwestern.at.utils.logger
Interface Logger

All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseLogger, DummyLogger, StandardErrorLogger
public interface Logger

Interface for a logger.

A logger is used to write messages to a log file. Each message has an associated level of severity. In increasing order these are:

  1. debug
  2. information
  3. warning
  4. error
  5. fatal

    6. Please see LoggerConstants for the associated numeric values for each level.
